    "body": "If a Cython file has the wrong extension--.py instead of .pyx, the Cython compiler generates misleading syntax errors when it encounters Cython keywords, as shown below:\r\n\r\n```\r\n>Cython bug.pyx\r\n\r\n>rename bug.pyx bug.py\r\n\r\n>Cython bug.py\r\n\r\nError compiling Cython file:\r\n-------------------------------------------------\r\n...\r\ncdef int add(int x, int y):\r\n    ^\r\n-------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nbug.py:1:5: Syntax error in simple statement list\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs it possible to get a more helpful error message, along the lines of the following?  \"Use of Cython keywords is not permitted in pure Python source files.\"",
